===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Used interchangeably with {{och-l|氒}} in oracle bone script. Likely a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of an arrow tip.

===Etymology===
Possibly {{der|zh|sit}}. Compare {{cog|bap|tr='''kʰok'''pa|t=old man}} ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 2017d}}), which STEDT derives from {{cog|sit-pro|*kwak||old}}.

{{och-l|舊|tr=*N-kʷəʔ-s}} may be a derivative ({{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). See there for more.

